            , and there he Received the King's pay and Cloaths, for the space of Two Months, and at Barnet he Received New Cloaths, and did his Duty as the part of a Souldier, but on the 20th. June did forsake his said Service, and ran away from his Majestys Camp on Hounslow-Heath, and about a Fortnight after, was found in Bridewell Committed as a Vagabond. The Prisoner said in his Defence, that truly he was a <rs id="t16860901-38-deflabel187" type="occupation">Souldier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t16860901-38-defend177 t16860901-38-deflabel187"></join>, and Received pay, but he did not go away, but with an intentent to return, not being sensible of the Danger of Running away from his Colours; and falling into ill Company he had sold his Cloaths, but he had left his Sword in the camp in his Tent; so upon a very full hearing of the Matter, and the Judges giving in their Opinions (Nemine Contradicente) that he ought to Dye for it; he was found <rs id="t16860901-38-verdict188" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16860901-38-verdict188" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
